4a:["$","p",null,{"children":["$","em",null,{"children":["Escape MDX-unsafe characters in text that appears outside code fences.  MDX parses ",["$","code",null,{"children":"<Word>"}]," as JSX tags and ",["$","code",null,{"children":"{expr}"}]," as JS expressions. In documentation content (summaries, descriptions, table cells), these come from TypeScript generics (",["$","code",null,{"children":"Array<string>"}],") and TSDoc inline tags (",["$","code",null,{"children":"{@link Foo}"}],"). We escape them so MDX treats them as literal text.  This is exported so SSG adapters can apply it during page transformation."]}]}]
